<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1769,2009]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[201,353,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male winged.</emphasis>
Similar to female in coloration but smaller; abdominal tergites II–VI with craspedum interrupted medially, with long and fine teeth; lateral thirds of tergites I–VIII covered with numerous irregular rows of microtrichia. Intermediate abdominal sternites without discal setae, sternites III–VIII with large transverse pore plates.
</paragraph>
